import datetime as dt
from collections import defaultdict

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap

plt.figure(figsize=(12,12))
event_map = Basemap(projection='merc', 
                    resolution='l', area_thresh=1000.0, # Low resolution
                    lat_0 = 55.0, lon_0=60.0, # Map center 
                    llcrnrlon=10, llcrnrlat=20, # Lower left corner
                    urcrnrlon=100, urcrnrlat=70) # Upper right corner

# Draw important features
event_map.drawcoastlines()
event_map.drawcountries()
event_map.fillcontinents(color='0.8')
event_map.drawmapboundary()

In [9]: 
with cursor_context() as cursor:
    sql = ("SELECT '{}', ST_AsGeoJSON(ST_Union(p.way)), ST_AsGeoJSON(ST_Buffer(ST_ConvexHull(ST_Union(p.way)), 0.0001)) "
           "FROM osm_polygon p, osm_polygon i "
           "WHERE i.osm_id = -59195 AND ST_Contains(i.way, p.way) AND "
           "p.tags->'addr:street' = '{}' AND p.tags->'addr:housenumber' IN ({}) "
           "GROUP BY 1")
    cursor.execute(' UNION '.join([
        sql.format(jes, street, ','.join(["'{}'".format(housnumber.strip()) for housnumber in str(housnumbers).split(',')]))
        for id, (jes, street, housnumbers) in jes_data[[' /', '  ', ' ']].iterrows()]))
    jes_houses_regions_data = list(cursor.fetchall())

In [13]: 
import base64
from IPython.display import HTML, display_html
import folium

folium.initialize_notebook()

def print_map(caption, street_hn, voronoi, region, houses):
    display_html(HTML('<h2>{}</h2>'.format(caption)))
    if street_hn:
        display_html(HTML('<table><tr><td>{}</td></tr></table>'.format(
            '</td></tr><tr><td>'.join(['{0}</td><td>{1}</td><td>{2}</td><td>{3}'.format(
                *['' if pd.isnull(arg) else arg for arg in args]) for args in street_hn])
        )))
    map = folium.Map(location=[53.9022756, 27.5618753], zoom_start=11, width=None)
    map.geo_json(geo_str=json.dumps(voronoi), fill_color='#00F', line_color='#00F')
    map.geo_json(geo_str=json.dumps(region), fill_color='#0F0', line_color='#0F0')
    map.geo_json(geo_str=json.dumps(houses), fill_color='#F00', line_color='#F00')
    map.create_map()
    display_html(HTML('<iframe src="data:text/html;base64,{}" style="width: 100%; height: 500px; border: none"></iframe>'.format(
                      base64.b64encode(bytes(map.HTML, 'utf8')).decode('ascii'))))
